IndieWebCamp

   Indie Web Camp 2014 by aaronpk

   IndieWebCamp is a gathering of web creators building & sharing open web
   technologies to advance the state of the indie web. We get together for
   a weekend to discuss how we can empower people to own their identities
   and data, then spend a day hacking & creating.

   See Previous IndieWebCamps, most recently the 2014 September Brighton
   UK, Main IndieWebCamp PDX/NYC/Berlin, April NYC, and March SF.
   IndieWebCamp has a code-of-conduct.

